  <section id="poems">
    <h2>Poetry</h2>

    <div class="poem">
      <div class="poem-title">Your Addiction</div>
      <div class="poem-content">
        “Your addiction — just infection of sublime yearning like a cancer,<br>
        Just handicapped hate like stammering disorder.”
      </div>
      <p><em>– When you're in love with someone you don't have</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="poem">
      <div class="poem-title">The Silence Between Us</div>
      <div class="poem-content">
        “Not every distance is measured in miles,<br>
        Sometimes it's the silence that separates souls.”
      </div>
      <p><em>– On unspoken love and fading connections</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="poem">
      <div class="poem-title">Stardust</div>
      <div class="poem-content">
        “We are not broken, we are just galaxies<br>
        Trying to find light in each other's chaos.”
      </div>
      <p><em>– On healing and hope</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="about">
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>Hi, I'm Shipra Yadav — a Diploma student in Information Technology at Government Girls Polytechnic, Varanasi. I'm passionate about coding and creative writing. I enjoy building simple web projects and writing emotionally charged poetry that reflects deep human experiences. I believe technology and art can coexist beautifully, and this site is my small attempt to show that fusion.</p>
